{{Han etyl}}

Uncertain. ''{{w|Shuowen}}'' considers it to be an {{Han compound|八|匸|ls=ic|ls2=psc|t1=eight|t2=to conceal|c1=p|c2=s|nocap=1}} – unit of measuring cloth. {{zh-l|*八}} refers to eight folds in one {{zh-l|*匹}} of cloth (two bolts of cloth), and {{zh-l|*匸}} refers to concealing the two ends of the cloth when rolling it up. This interpretation is not likely since the older forms evidently do not contain these components.

Various theories have been proposed based on the evidence from the bronze inscriptions:
* {{liushu|p}} of folds in cloth ({{zh-ref|Lin, 1920}});
* {{liushu|i}}: half of {{zh-l|*丙|two horses}} – one horse ({{zh-ref|Zhang et al., 1996}});
* {{Han compound|石|乙|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=rock}} or {{ltc-l|乀}}. The phonetic component may be replaced with {{och-l|匕|id=1}} (not shown above).

